```tsx
type A1 =
  /* 1 */ | /* 2 */ (
    /* 3 */ | /* 4 */ {
        key: string;
      }
  );

```

**Output:**
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
```tsx
type A1 /* 2 */ = /* 1 */ /* 3 */ /* 4 */ {
  key: string;
};

```

**Expected output:**
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
```tsx
type A1 = /* 1 */ /* 2 */ /* 3 */ /* 4 */ {
  key: string;
};
```

**Why?**

Comment `/* 2 */` moves from after `=` to before `=`. This changes the comment from annotating the type value to annotating the type name. The reordering of comments seems arbitrary.


